<subSubSection id="C37C6FCF4019FF8AFF7BFE1FFB81FD29" pageId="1" pageNumber="382" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD93C444019FF8AFF7BFE1FFB81FD29" blockId="1.[151,1437,510,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis id="B912E0564019FF8AFF7BFE1FFEE3FD98" bold="true" box="[151,274,510,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body medium. Wings absent. Male hind femora armed on ventral surface. Hind tibiae of male distinctly curved, with strongly reduced spines on dorsal surface and undulate on ventral surface; while female hind femora less strongly specialized. Male ninth abdominal tergite cuculli-form, posterior area obviously divided into 2 lateral lobes or spines, distinctly curved ventrad, emargination between them deep and triangular; subgenital plate without styli, posterior margin with a deep and wide concavity and with apices digitate laterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
